HEADWORD: Dobells solution
<hw>Do*bell's" so*lu"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An
aqueous solution of carbolic acid, borax, sodium bicarbonate, and
glycerin, used as a spray in diseases of the nose and throat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

